Time Complexity:

Let n = size of nums1  
Let m = size of nums2

    Building map → O(m)
    For each element in nums1:
        scan nums2 → O(m)

Overall: O(n * m)


Space Complexity:

    HashMap stores indices of nums2 → O(m)

Overall: O(m)


Approach:

1. Create a HashMap:
   - Store element → index mapping of nums2

2. Traverse nums1:
   - For each element, find its index in nums2 using map

3. Start searching to the right of that index:
   - Move forward until you find element greater than current

4. If found:
   - Store that value in nums1

5. If not found:
   - Store -1

6. Return modified nums1 as result






class Solution {
    public int[] nextGreaterElement(int[] nums1, int[] nums2) {
        HashMap<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < nums2.length; i++) {
            map.put(nums2[i], i);
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < nums1.length; i++) {
            int j = map.get(nums1[i]) + 1;
            while (j < nums2.length && nums2[j] < nums1[i])
                j++;
            if (j == nums2.length)
                nums1[i] = -1;
            else
                nums1[i] = nums2[j];
        }
        return nums1;
    }
}
